# API Guidelines

## REST Conventions

- Use consistent HTTP verbs: GET (read), POST (create), PUT/PATCH (update), DELETE.
- Return appropriate status codes: 200, 201, 400, 401, 404, 500.
- Validate input with Zod (TS) or Pydantic (Python).

## Response Format

Prefer consistent JSON structure:
```json
{ "success": true, "data": {...} }
{ "success": false, "error": "message" }
```

## Error Handling

- Handle errors at the beginning of functions with early returns.
- Use user-friendly error messages.
- Log server-side errors, return sanitized messages to client.
